Recall that $x^2 - y^2$ factors as $(x+y)(x-y)$. So we have:
$$\frac{(x+y)(x-y)}{x+y}$$

When $x+y \neq 0$, we can cancel $(x+y)$ from the numerator and denominator, leaving us with $x-y$. 

